Afrihost and MWEB have launched new Rain-based LTE-A “double data” deals. This follows other local ISPs launching the new LTE-A deals. New and existing customers will benefit from the promotion, which doubles the data allocation of current packages and introduces new, higher-cap packages – which also include a double-data allotment. The additional monthly data will be in place until November 2018. Customers must sign up before 30 November 2017 in order to benefit from the promotion Customers are required to purchase a Huawei router to use the Rain network, which provides speeds of between 10Mbps-50Mbps, and coverage is limited to certain areas.